      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl5-requirements",
      "rationale": "CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R1) operates under ISO 9001-compliant SQA plan. Version control, regression testing, and release validation documented. Achieved Gradation 3: solver verified against benchmark suite; user modification log maintained. Meets MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests performed on canonical rotating-channel and pipe-flow problems. Observed convergence rate 1.92 (expected 2.0 for second-order scheme); deviation within acceptable tolerance. Method of Manufactured Solutions applied to hemolysis transport equation. Achieves Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M cells). GCI computed per Roache methodology; fine-mesh GCI < 1.8% for hemolysis index QoI. Richardson extrapolation applied. Achieves Gradation 4, exceeding MRL 5 requirement of Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements conducted at five operating points (flow rates 3–7 L/min, speeds 2400–3600 RPM) matching CFD boundary conditions. Temperature, hematocrit, and blood analog properties documented and matched. Gradation 3 achieved: conditions well-characterized with quantified uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index predictions compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute error 8.3%; all predictions within experimental uncertainty bands (±15%). Validation metric computed per ASME V&V 20. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed from predicted shear stress and exposure time via power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger model. NIH directly maps to clinical hemolysis threshold. QoI traceability from model output to regulatory acceptance criterion fully documented. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — same device class and flow regime as COU. Operating conditions span the COU envelope. Blood analog (porcine RBC suspension) is clinically representative. Gradation 3 achieved: high geometric and physiological relevance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (all below 1e-6) and integral QoI stabilization. Round-off error estimated negligible at double precision. Solver error budget quantified and found to be less than 0.5% of total uncertainty. Exceeds Gradation 2 requirement; Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst. Boundary condition specification, turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), and hemolysis model parameter inputs verified against published reference setup. Checklist-based review completed with zero critical findings. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5",
      "rationale": "RANS SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark performance for rotating confined flows. Hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) validated against in-vitro Couette and capillary data. Model form uncertainty quantified via comparison with LES-derived shear stress distribution at design point. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl5",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions, hemolysis model coefficients) characterized with uncertainty distributions. Monte Carlo propagation (10,000 samples) performed. Input sensitivity analysis (Sobol indices) identifies hemolysis model exponents as dominant contributors. Full input uncertainty budget documented. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "This factor addresses physical test article sampling variability as defined in NASA-STD-7009A for hardware qualification programs. Under ASME V&V 40-2018 for this medical-device CFD credibility assessment, test sample variability is subsumed within the 'Test conditions' and 'Equivalency of input parameters' factors. No physical pump hardware samples are assessed in this V&V activity; the FDA generic pump is a computational reference geometry. Factor is not applicable to this ASME V&V 40 COU context."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "This factor as defined in NASA-STD-7009A concerns equivalency between flight and test article input parameters for aerospace hardware. In this ASME V&V 40 medical-device CFD context, the computational model directly uses the same geometric and operational inputs as the validation experiments; there is no distinction between 'test article' and 'flight article' configurations. Input parameter equivalency is fully addressed within the 'Model inputs' and 'Test conditions' factors assessed above. Factor is not applicable to this V&V 40 COU."
    }
