  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-accepted-nc6",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 11 assessed credibility factors achieve their required levels under ASME V&V 40-2018 at Model Risk Level 5. Three factors (Discretization error, Numerical solver error, Use error) exceed their required levels, providing additional confidence margin. Two factors (Test samples, Equivalency of input parameters) are marked not-applicable with documented rationale: these factors originate from NASA-STD-7009A aerospace hardware qualification contexts and are not applicable to this medical-device CFD V&V 40 assessment, where their content is fully subsumed by the assessed Test conditions and Model inputs factors respectively. The provenance chain is complete: all ValidationResults link to experimental datasets, generating activities, and UQ analyses. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (10,000 samples) confirms hemolysis index predictions remain below the clinical threshold across the full input uncertainty space. The credibility evidence package is sufficient to support regulatory submission for this Class III VAD device under the stated COU.",
